╭─ Assistant [MainThread@1659129] ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────╮
│ Based on the root cause analysis, the crash occurs because `vectorizeCmpInsts` is called   │
│ with a list of `CmpInst*` which may contain dangling pointers to instructions that have    │
│ already been deleted by a previous vectorization step. The initial analysis suggested that │
│ this call was redundant and could be removed. However, removing it caused multiple test    │
│ regressions, indicating that this separate vectorization path for compares is necessary in │
│ some cases.                                                                                │
│                                                                                            │
│ The correct approach is to ensure that `vectorizeCmpInsts` is not called with dangling     │
│ pointers. This can be achieved by filtering the list of `CmpInst*` to remove any           │
│ instructions that have been deleted (i.e., their parent basic block is null).              │
│                                                                                            │
│ The bug is located in `vectorizeChainsInBlock`. This function collects all `CmpInst`s from │
│ the basic block into a `CmpInsts` vector. After attempting to vectorize other instruction  │
│ chains (which might delete some of the compares), it then calls `vectorizeCmpInsts` with   │
│ this potentially stale list.                                                               │
│                                                                                            │
│ The fix is to add a check before calling `vectorizeCmpInsts` to remove any deleted         │
│ instructions from the `CmpInsts` list.                                                     │
│                                                                                            │
│ ```patch                                                                                   │
│ --- a/llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp                                      │
│ +++ b/llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp                                      │
│ @@ -21540,9 +21540,13 @@                                                                   │
│      Changed |= VectorizeInsertsAndCmps(/*VectorizeCmps=*/true);                           │
│    }                                                                                       │
│                                                                                            │
│ -  if (!CmpInsts.empty())                                                                  │
│ -    Changed |= vectorizeCmpInsts(make_range(CmpInsts.rbegin(), CmpInsts.rend()),          │
│ -                                 BB, R);                                                  │
│ +  if (!CmpInsts.empty()) {                                                                │
│ +    // Remove instructions that may have been deleted by the vectorizer.                  │
│ +    llvm::erase_if(CmpInsts, [](Instruction *I) { return !I->getParent(); });             │
│ +    if (!CmpInsts.empty())                                                                │
│ +      Changed |= vectorizeCmpInsts(                                                       │
│ +          make_range(CmpInsts.rbegin(), CmpInsts.rend()), BB, R);                         │
│ +  }                                                                                       │
│                                                                                            │
│    return Changed;                                                                         │
│  }                                                                                         │
│                                                                                            │
│ ```                                                                                        │
